    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n3177" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐνίπτω</span></b> , opt. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐνίπτοι</span>, imp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔνιπτε</span>, aor. 2 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐνένῑπε</span>
          and <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἠνίπαπε</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">chide, rebuke,
            upbraid;</span> Odysseus chides himself, to repress his wrath,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κραδίην ἠνίπαπε μύ̄θῳ:</span> | ‘<span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τέτλαθι δή, κραδίη, υ’</span> 17; usually w.
          specifying terms in dat., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χαλεποῖσιν ὀνείδεσιν,
            ὀνειδείοις ἐπέεσσιν, χαλεπῷ</span> or <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κακῷ
            μύ̄θῳ,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 2.245</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 3.438</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> Ρ 141</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 18.326</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
